oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Panoramic photograph of soldiers on a shooting range
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This panoramic photograph shows American soldiers seated and firing at targets while officers or non-commissioned officers chart their marksmanship behind the firing line. A thrid row of men await their turn on the line. The men are wearing the Model 1911 Army Campaign Hat which indicates that this photograph was taken in the United States. The donor believed the images was taken at Warner Park in Nashville.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: World War, 1914-1918; World War, 1914-1918 - History
